			<title>Citizens Beyond Walls Preparation Meeting Berlin</title>
			<link>http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/citizens-beyond-walls/254-citizens-beyond-walls-update-berlin</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/citizens-beyond-walls/254-citizens-beyond-walls-update-berlin</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p style="line-height: 150%;"><span><span style="font-size: 9pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana;">The kick-off of the Citizens Beyond Walls project was the 19th - 22nd of December in Berlin. A weekend in where all the project coordinators and main researchers came together to discuss the content of the project. In Berlin we defined the important concepts within this project (what do we mean with extreme right wing growth and is this the same for all the countries?), the different levels of research (within civil society, on the extra-parliamentary level), the main issues in the different European countries and we formulated common aims to bring the research of all the countries together.</span></span></p>
</div>]]></description>
